You're asking me?</i>

61
00:09:17,493 --> 00:09:20,559
Since when do they lock churches
in this country, huh?

62
00:09:23,061 --> 00:09:25,811
This is a sacred place. Protected.

63
00:09:25,878 --> 00:09:28,017
<i>Well, l didn't steal anything.</i>

64
00:09:28,982 --> 00:09:30,356
You an American?

65
00:09:45,625 --> 00:09:47,600
<i>Look, l don't need any trouble.</i>

66
00:09:47,770 --> 00:09:50,771
l heard about this place.
l had to find a way in.

67
00:09:51,035 --> 00:09:52,561
What is this?

68
00:09:53,499 --> 00:09:56,281
<i>They're figure studies for a graphic novel.</i>

69
00:09:59,003 --> 00:10:00,149
Like...

70
00:10:03,260 --> 00:10:04,569
Like these.

71
00:10:05,725 --> 00:10:08,595
-Which one has the wolves?
-The next one.

72
00:10:10,462 --> 00:10:12,950
<i>My name's Aiden. Aiden Galvin.</i>

73
00:10:13,022 --> 00:10:14,811
<i>l'm here for research.</i>

74
00:10:15,134 --> 00:10:16,662
And trespassing.

75
00:10:18,750 --> 00:10:21,948
Look. Bucharest is a treasure trove.

76
00:10:22,688 --> 00:10:25,984
<i>l'd heard there were places
that wolves were almost, like, worshipped.</i>

77
00:10:26,048 --> 00:10:28,569
<i>But l didn't think they meant it literally.</i>

78
00:10:28,641 --> 00:10:31,641
<i>Strictly speaking,
they're not actually wolves.</i>

79
00:10:31,745 --> 00:10:33,884
<i>They were called Ioup-garous.</i>

80
00:10:35,554 --> 00:10:37,278
You mean werewolves.

81
00:10:38,051 --> 00:10:39,993
Not as you and l think of them.

82
00:10:41,250 --> 00:10:44,251
<i>They weren't monsters,
not in the legends here.</i>

83
00:10:45,220 --> 00:10:48,570
-What were they, then?
-They were revered.

84
00:10:49,829 --> 00:10:52,131
They were the best of man,
the best of beast.

85
00:10:52,197 --> 00:10:55,645
Kind of shape-shifters, l guess.
Until they were wiped out.

86
00:10:55,749 --> 00:10:57,473
ln the legends.

87
00:11:05,799 --> 00:11:08,734
-So your comic book...
-Graphic novel.

88
00:11:09,959 --> 00:11:11,847
<i>lt's not about monsters?</i>

89
00:11:13,577 --> 00:11:15,366
Just us humans, right?

90
00:11:17,833 --> 00:11:21,314
Hey, were you hiding or something?
What are you doing here?

91
00:11:22,506 --> 00:11:25,322
<i>Wait, wait, wait, wait.
l'm leaving, all right, l'm outta here.</i>

92
00:11:25,387 --> 00:11:27,209
Just tell me your name.

93
00:11:28,619 --> 00:11:30,627
You do have a name, right?

94
00:11:32,428 --> 00:11:34,087
Do they have names?

95
00:11:37,388 --> 00:11:38,818
Why should we?

96
00:11:40,301 --> 00:11:42,790
<i>lt's bad luck to break into a church.</i>

97
00:11:43,405 --> 00:11:44,999
<i>Hey, what's your name?</i>

98
00:11:57,616 --> 00:11:59,177
<i>l don't want to come.</i>

99
00:11:59,697 --> 00:12:02,567
Go. Go, go, go!

100
00:12:53,275 --> 00:12:55,511
Let me in! Help! Please!

101
00:13:05,756 --> 00:13:07,284
Get out of here.

102
00:13:18,366 --> 00:13:22,044
<i>Oh, come on now, cousin.
lt's not like we were going to hurt her.</i>

103
00:13:23,007 --> 00:13:25,179
You have to let the boys have their fun.

104
00:13:25,248 --> 00:13:26,840
You know the law.

105
00:13:27,424 --> 00:13:28,537
The law.

106
00:13:28,609 --> 00:13:31,260
<i>What's one girl, right? And another.</i>

107
00:13:31,329 --> 00:13:33,785
<i>When they come,
they'll come in numbers with guns.</i>

108
00:13:33,858 --> 00:13:35,898
<i>And not just for you.
They'll come for all of us.</i>

109
00:13:35,970 --> 00:13:37,758
<i>Spoken like a bitch who's been there.</i>

110
00:13:37,825 --> 00:13:41,504
<i>We weren't gonna hurt her, Vivian.
We were just playing games.</i>

111
00:13:41,571 --> 00:13:43,480
We know the risks, Vivian, same as you.

112
00:13:43,555 --> 00:13:46,752
<i>Yes, see, we all know Gabriel's law.</i>

113
00:13:46,819 --> 00:13:50,715
<i>-''Hunt as a pack or not at all.''
-''Hunt as a pack or not at all.''</i>

114
00:13:54,244 --> 00:13:56,252
<i>And the laws he'll have for you.</i>

115
00:14:05,447 --> 00:14:06,909
<i>She's asleep.</i>

116
00:14:10,376 --> 00:14:11,586
Gabriel,

117
00:14:13,448 --> 00:14:15,750
she stayed home waiting for you.

118
00:14:18,409 --> 00:14:20,165
Are you afraid of me?

119
00:14:21,386 --> 00:14:22,334
No.

120
00:14:26,058 --> 00:14:28,066
You know about our tradition.

121
00:14:28,139 --> 00:14:31,009
Every seven years,
the leader of the pack takes a new wife.

122
00:14:31,083 --> 00:14:32,774
<i>Don't you mean mate?</i>

123
00:14:35,019 --> 00:14:39,079
Should show more respect for the rules.
Without them we cannot survive.

124
00:14:40,205 --> 00:14:41,896
There are prophecies

125
00:14:42,989 --> 00:14:44,900
about girls like you.

126
00:14:48,270 --> 00:14:50,824
You come from a long line of leaders,
you know.

127
00:14:50,894 --> 00:14:54,026
Women in your family
were legends in this city.

128
00:14:55,183 --> 00:14:57,965
Your father should never have gone
to America.

129
00:14:58,031 --> 00:14:59,974
l knew how he would end. l told him.

130
00:15:00,048 --> 00:15:01,958
You must have hated him very much.

131
00:15:02,033 --> 00:15:04,968
No.
But you know why we have survived here?

132
00:15:06,545 --> 00:15:08,750
<i>lt's because we stand together.</i>

133
00:15:09,586 --> 00:15:12,073
Your father thought of himself first.

134
00:15:12,915 --> 00:15:14,541
<i>Don't insult my family.</i>

135
00:15:14,611 --> 00:15:17,197
You have no family. You have heritage.

136
00:15:29,526 --> 00:15:31,947
<i>lf you're the one from the prophesy,</i>

137
00:15:33,366 --> 00:15:35,701
soon l will ask you to be my wife.

138
00:15:37,943 --> 00:15:39,983
l see what you did to Astrid.

139
00:15:40,727 --> 00:15:43,149
You come for one night,
she cries for a month.

140
00:15:43,224 --> 00:15:46,224
<i>You want to be ordinary?
You're not ordinary.</i>

141
00:15:50,329 --> 00:15:53,678
Ask the animal who is inside you.
She will teach you.

142
00:16:37,409 --> 00:16:38,490
Fear.

143
00:16:41,218 --> 00:16:43,520
Was l not worthy of your respect?

144
00:16:46,210 --> 00:16:48,993
No trace of admiration?

145
00:16:52,836 --> 00:16:56,098
<i>That's because you don't know the real me.</i>

146
00:17:41,644 --> 00:17:44,809
Hey, scumbag, you are free to go.

147
00:17:46,574 --> 00:17:50,829
Detectives? Where are you taking me? Huh?

148
00:17:50,894 --> 00:17:53,709
What is this? Where are you taking me?

149
00:18:18,228 --> 00:18:20,945
My friend, your arrest has made the paper.

150
00:18:22,131 --> 00:18:23,626
You must be very proud.

151
00:18:23,700 --> 00:18:26,515
What is this? And who are you?

152
00:18:27,957 --> 00:18:30,062
Please, have a drink with me.

153
00:18:31,958 --> 00:18:34,773
<i>Absinthe, it's an old ritual of mine.</i>

154
00:18:38,391 --> 00:18:40,726
Why did you pay to get me out?

155
00:18:42,551 --> 00:18:43,500
Drink.

156
00:18:50,680 --> 00:18:54,161
You know, there are countries
where they call this poison.

157
00:18:54,554 --> 00:18:58,962
<i>Of course, it doesn't come in a dirty needle.
And it's not sold to children.</i>

158
00:19:00,730 --> 00:19:03,731
What you want? You want a cut?

159
00:19:04,923 --> 00:19:06,265
You want in?

160
00:19:06,332 --> 00:19:09,977
My friend,
you have escaped the law till now.

161
00:19:10,268 --> 00:19:12,658
But in this city, we are the law.

162
00:19:13,245 --> 00:19:15,863
As we have been for 5,000 years.

163
00:19:20,926 --> 00:19:24,243
<i>We'll find out
who you've been selling your poison to.</i>

164
00:19:24,767 --> 00:19:27,549
For tomorrow, tradition reigns.

165
00:19:31,489 --> 00:19:34,008
Well, that makes all the difference.

166
00:19:55,716 --> 00:19:58,586
<i>-Your chocolates.
-That's so nice. Thanks.</i>

167
00:20:37,740 --> 00:20:40,424
Hey! Hey, Wolf-Girl!

168
00:22:36,288 --> 00:22:38,677
Hello, sweet tooth. Ready to hunt?

169
00:22:40,098 --> 00:22:43,262
All hail the queen of the night,
the beauty of Bucharest!

170
00:22:43,330 --> 00:22:45,403
She will hunt and hunt supreme.

171
00:22:45,474 --> 00:22:47,132
Mama.

172
00:22:55,331 --> 00:22:56,958
<i>Willem, so he's chasing the meat, right?</i>

173
00:22:57,029 --> 00:22:59,517
<i>Lands on it, turns it around, it's Gregor.</i>

174
00:23:01,061 --> 00:23:02,468
-Did l tell you?
-No, l had no idea.

175
00:23:02,534 --> 00:23:03,678
l had no idea.

176
00:23:20,808 --> 00:23:22,369
Hell of a night.

177
00:23:55,726 --> 00:23:58,541
<i>''ln fear l hurried this way and that.</i>

178
00:23:58,606 --> 00:24:01,771
<i>''l had the taste of blood and chocolate
in my mouth,</i>

179
00:24:01,839 --> 00:24:05,418
<i>''the one as hateful as the other.''
Remember that?</i>

180
00:24:05,904 --> 00:24:07,246
<i>SteppenwoIf.</i>

181
00:24:07,888 --> 00:24:10,059
<i>We're all lost souls, Vivian.</i>

182
00:24:11,921 --> 00:24:14,224
<i>At least we're lost together.</i>

183
00:24:56,633 --> 00:24:58,640
My lords and ladies,

184
00:24:58,713 --> 00:25:01,911
we gather tonight
as our ancestors did for all time.

185
00:25:02,203 --> 00:25:05,945
The first night of the full moon
when we gather as one.

186
00:25:06,106 --> 00:25:07,568
For we are one.

187
00:25:09,083 --> 00:25:10,741
And we hunt as one.

188
00:25:12,860 --> 00:25:16,920
We have survived for 5,000 years
by hiding who we are.

189
00:25:18,652 --> 00:25:22,582
We have been chased from everywhere,
England, France, America,

190
00:25:23,741 --> 00:25:25,171
but not here.

191
00:25:25,982 --> 00:25:27,324
Never here.

192
00:25:29,822 --> 00:25:32,670
This thing before you

193
00:25:35,135 --> 00:25:36,598
is called man.

194
00:25:37,536 --> 00:25:40,318
But l call it menace.

195
00:25:41,985 --> 00:25:44,506
The race of man is corrupt at its core.

196
00:25:45,058 --> 00:25:48,125
<i>The only thing it's good at is destruction!</i>

197
00:25:48,194 --> 00:25:50,616
And so, once in a while,
we must make an example

198
00:25:50,691 --> 00:25:53,887
to show this menace
that we may be outnumbered,

199
00:25:54,243 --> 00:25:56,513
but we will never be outhunted.

200
00:26:08,742 --> 00:26:10,335
So on this night,

201
00:26:13,062 --> 00:26:15,201
let nature grace us to return

202
00:26:15,847 --> 00:26:17,570
to who we truly are

203
00:26:18,279 --> 00:26:21,695
in the wild where we once lived.

204
00:26:36,587 --> 00:26:38,475
Please. l swear...

205
00:26:38,635 --> 00:26:41,023
There is a river within those woods.

206
00:26:42,700 --> 00:26:45,482
lf you reach the other side,
you win your life.

207
00:26:45,932 --> 00:26:47,427
And if not,

208
00:26:47,980 --> 00:26:50,250
<i>glory to the Ioup-garou who takes it.</i>

209
00:26:57,486 --> 00:26:58,697
Run free.

210
00:27:03,247 --> 00:27:06,029
No one ever reaches the river.

211
00:28:24,253 --> 00:28:25,497
Help me!

212
00:29:34,538 --> 00:29:36,099
<i>lt's who you are</i>

213
00:29:37,418 --> 00:29:39,077
and always will be.

214
00:30:26,515 --> 00:30:29,101
Help! Help!

215
00:31:15,323 --> 00:31:19,797
<i>Bunâ, any mail for me? Letters, packages?
l'm in 204.</i>

216
00:31:20,028 --> 00:31:21,490
No mail today.

217
00:31:22,364 --> 00:31:23,958
Did you even check?

218
00:31:24,252 --> 00:31:25,943
No mail for nobody.

219
00:31:34,334 --> 00:31:35,350
<i>Where'd you get this?</i>

220
00:31:38,240 --> 00:31:40,412
Yes, l am being careful. Thank you.

221
00:31:40,992 --> 00:31:43,097
<i>Why don't you go sell something
for a change?</i>

222
00:31:47,073 --> 00:31:50,041
<i>lt's not gonna taste any better
with you standing there watching me.</i>

223
00:31:50,114 --> 00:31:51,575
Hey, Wolf-Girl.

224
00:31:54,114 --> 00:31:56,002
<i>Don't ever call me that.</i>

225
00:31:56,162 --> 00:31:58,651
So give me something else to call you.

226
00:31:58,723 --> 00:32:00,414
How did you find me?

227
00:32:00,643 --> 00:32:01,853
Find who?

228
00:32:03,652 --> 00:32:04,797
Vivian.

229
00:32:06,277 --> 00:32:07,454
<i>Look, l'm working. l can't talk.</i>

230
00:32:07,524 --> 00:32:09,412
<i>And l really don't think
you should be back here.</i>

231
00:32:09,477 --> 00:32:11,103
So ask me to leave.

232
00:32:14,278 --> 00:32:15,227
Leave.

233
00:32:17,415 --> 00:32:19,520
Now ask me like you mean it.

234
00:32:19,654 --> 00:32:21,956
<i>What's it been, two, three weeks?</i>

235
00:32:22,022 --> 00:32:24,445
What are you still doing in Romania?

236
00:32:24,807 --> 00:32:26,302
Trying to work.

237
00:32:28,391 --> 00:32:31,557
<i>-Don't you have a home to go back to?
-No, l don't.</i>

238
00:32:32,489 --> 00:32:34,594
But l do have a train ticket in a few days.

239
00:32:34,665 --> 00:32:37,601
And l was hoping
to spend some of them with you.

240
00:32:38,026 --> 00:32:41,507
<i>Yeah, well, that wouldn't make my boyfriend
really happy.</i>

241
00:32:41,738 --> 00:32:42,686
Oh.

242
00:32:44,651 --> 00:32:48,679
Would you be at a church at 2:00
in the morning if you had a boyfriend?

243
00:32:54,605 --> 00:32:57,573
<i>Why do you always run from me?
That's twice now, you've run from me.</i>

244
