00:55:51,337 --> 00:55:55,975
<i>So your playmate's home tonight.
You should come see me.</i>

474
00:55:56,042 --> 00:55:57,897
Not tonight, Astrid.

475
00:55:58,250 --> 00:56:00,323
These old laws, you can change them.

476
00:56:00,394 --> 00:56:03,623
Seven years, why seven?
Real wolves mate for life.

477
00:56:03,882 --> 00:56:05,825
Not another word.

478
00:56:07,691 --> 00:56:11,620
Come on. We used to set this place on fire.

479
00:56:14,189 --> 00:56:18,827
We all grow old, Astrid.
We have to do it with dignity.

480
00:56:44,658 --> 00:56:47,113
Aiden? What...

481
00:56:47,666 --> 00:56:51,408
Aiden, what happened?

482
00:56:51,506 --> 00:56:52,684
Your cousin.

483
00:56:52,787 --> 00:56:55,635
-Rafe? What are you...
-Stay back.

484
00:56:56,723 --> 00:56:59,090
Why do you know so much about wolves,
Vivian?

485
00:56:59,156 --> 00:57:01,261
What are you talking about?
How badly are you hurt?

486
00:57:01,332 --> 00:57:04,267
<i>ls it 'cause you knew he was one, huh?</i>

487
00:57:04,340 --> 00:57:08,235
<i>Loup-garou. Like the legend.
Like a comic book.</i>

488
00:57:10,165 --> 00:57:11,988
Where is he?

489
00:57:12,886 --> 00:57:14,380
Extinct.

490
00:57:23,320 --> 00:57:24,913
Take it.

491
00:57:28,664 --> 00:57:31,698
<i>Go on, take it. lt's silver.</i>

492
00:57:35,641 --> 00:57:39,832
-l wanted to protect you.
-Protect me from who? From you?

493
00:57:40,314 --> 00:57:41,841
<i>You're not possible.</i>

494
00:57:41,915 --> 00:57:44,817
Get out of town. Get out of Romania.
Get out and never come back.

495
00:57:44,891 --> 00:57:46,385
<i>lf they find you, they'll kill you.</i>

496
00:57:46,459 --> 00:57:47,604
<i>Oh, it's ''they'' now, huh?</i>

497
00:57:47,675 --> 00:57:49,334
What did you want from me, the truth?

498
00:57:49,403 --> 00:57:51,770
Listen, my life is over. l just killed someone!

499
00:57:51,868 --> 00:57:55,665
<i>They're gonna find my prints, my blood.
What am l gonna tell them?</i>

500
00:57:56,188 --> 00:57:58,610
What will you tell them?

501
00:57:58,685 --> 00:58:02,482
<i>lt's just too much to ask, l guess,
just a human girl.</i>

502
00:58:02,653 --> 00:58:05,141
<i>-Aiden, l never wanted...
-lt's too late for that.</i>

503
00:58:06,142 --> 00:58:11,031
<i>lf you cared a goddamn thing about me,
you would've left me before we ever met.</i>

504
00:58:20,512 --> 00:58:22,301
Aiden.

505
00:59:21,833 --> 00:59:24,005
May l help you, sir?

506
00:59:26,219 --> 00:59:29,383
Yes, as a matter of fact you can.

507
00:59:31,339 --> 00:59:33,674
Are these real silver?

508
00:59:33,836 --> 00:59:35,559
Of course.

509
00:59:35,628 --> 00:59:37,351
Thank you.

510
00:59:52,558 --> 00:59:54,860
We went to find him.

511
00:59:58,608 --> 01:00:01,358
<i>He'd been gone for so long.</i>

512
01:00:33,781 --> 01:00:36,083
What is it, Vivian?

513
01:00:37,110 --> 01:00:39,281
<i>His car's outside.</i>

514
01:00:58,648 --> 01:01:00,274
<i>What's happened?</i>

515
01:01:02,361 --> 01:01:04,085
Our son is dead.

516
01:01:21,756 --> 01:01:24,277
He will be avenged.

517
01:01:45,696 --> 01:01:47,256
Do you need some help?

518
01:01:47,328 --> 01:01:50,842
<i>No. No, thank you, Officers.
l'm just waiting for my train.</i>

519
01:01:51,137 --> 01:01:53,047
The correct answer is yes.

520
01:02:27,079 --> 01:02:29,567
My lords and ladies.

521
01:02:31,079 --> 01:02:35,236
Man has forced us to hide our true nature.

522
01:02:35,368 --> 01:02:38,020
He has persecuted us for centuries.

523
01:02:40,297 --> 01:02:43,297
Last night, he took yet another life.

524
01:02:46,954 --> 01:02:49,093
The life of my son.

525
01:02:52,427 --> 01:02:57,032
But we will have vengeance,
for his murderer is here.

526
01:03:02,636 --> 01:03:04,546
No!

527
01:03:04,973 --> 01:03:05,922
Him!

528
01:03:05,996 --> 01:03:06,979
Rafe went to kill him.

529
01:03:07,053 --> 01:03:11,178
This man knew our secret
because one of us let him get too near.

530
01:03:11,246 --> 01:03:13,254
And how would you know that?

531
01:03:14,670 --> 01:03:17,289
Did Rafe hunt him down on his own,
or did you send him?

532
01:03:17,359 --> 01:03:19,148
He killed my son.
He must pay with his blood.

533
01:03:19,215 --> 01:03:21,452
You sent your own son to his death
over me?

534
01:03:21,519 --> 01:03:23,658
Enough!

535
01:03:27,921 --> 01:03:31,216
lf he lives,
he will bring the hunters in the night.

536
01:03:31,473 --> 01:03:35,816
Just like the ones who killed your parents.
And it will be all your fault again.

537
01:03:43,442 --> 01:03:45,712
<i>There's a river within those woods.</i>

538
01:03:45,779 --> 01:03:48,681
lf you reach the other side,
you win your life.

539
01:03:50,004 --> 01:03:51,379
No.

540
01:03:53,748 --> 01:03:55,504
Wish your enemy well.

541
01:04:00,341 --> 01:04:02,164
Wish him well.

542
01:04:29,914 --> 01:04:31,540
Run.

543
01:05:20,866 --> 01:05:24,096
You say man is a heartless killer.
How are we any different?

544
01:05:24,226 --> 01:05:26,267
We only kill to survive.

545
01:05:27,235 --> 01:05:29,243
Take her to the car till l come back.

546
01:05:48,103 --> 01:05:50,372
<i>Stupid girl. You are Ioup-garou.</i>

547
01:07:45,048 --> 01:07:48,016
Creeks lead to rivers.

548
01:09:42,699 --> 01:09:44,521
But l crossed the river.

549
01:09:45,004 --> 01:09:46,465
The river.

550
01:10:27,826 --> 01:10:30,444
What about your goddamn river, huh?

551
01:10:58,839 --> 01:11:01,589
Oh, Jesus, no.

552
01:11:10,328 --> 01:11:12,565
<i>l'm sorry, l...</i>

553
01:11:33,660 --> 01:11:36,726
<i>Please don't kill me.</i>

554
01:11:52,223 --> 01:11:57,526
<i>Hold on, there's a road ahead.
We have to get you to a hospital.</i>

555
01:11:57,760 --> 01:12:00,663
No, hospitals only make it worse.

556
01:12:01,025 --> 01:12:02,716
Then where?

557
01:12:04,481 --> 01:12:06,304
<i>There's a place.</i>

558
01:12:50,569 --> 01:12:53,864
Vivian! You home, little girl?

559
01:12:58,602 --> 01:13:02,465
<i>They won't look for us here.
This is a film company.</i>

560
01:13:02,699 --> 01:13:05,481
Do you know what makes
photographs work?

561
01:13:05,611 --> 01:13:07,498
Silver.

562
01:13:10,059 --> 01:13:14,762
<i>They say, even now,
it'll kill you to breathe it.</i>

563
01:13:15,084 --> 01:13:16,426
Will it?

564
01:13:16,493 --> 01:13:19,177
<i>lt's already in my bloodstream.</i>

565
01:13:19,629 --> 01:13:23,623
<i>Once it's in, it stays in, unless it's treated.</i>

566
01:13:24,558 --> 01:13:25,965
Treated how?

567
01:13:26,030 --> 01:13:30,024
<i>There's an anti-serum for silver
called Antigen-AG.</i>

568
01:13:30,895 --> 01:13:33,317
l know where l can find some
but not until dark.

569
01:13:35,344 --> 01:13:36,871
Come on.

570
01:13:41,936 --> 01:13:43,759
Vivian!

571
01:13:58,290 --> 01:13:59,981
<i>You didn't leave.</i>

572
01:14:01,427 --> 01:14:03,816
<i>l'm running out of people to trust.</i>

573
01:14:04,628 --> 01:14:06,897
<i>l've never killed anyone.</i>

574
01:14:07,444 --> 01:14:10,444
At the hunts. Please believe me.

575
01:14:10,676 --> 01:14:13,459
Why do you even go?

576
01:14:15,285 --> 01:14:19,661
<i>lt's not the hunt l live for. lt's the running.</i>

577
01:14:20,598 --> 01:14:23,152
The being free.

578
01:14:24,887 --> 01:14:28,400
They were my tracks the hunters followed
back to our house.

579
01:14:30,488 --> 01:14:32,113
<i>That doesn't make it your fault.</i>

580
01:14:32,184 --> 01:14:34,486
Men kill us. We kill men.

581
01:14:34,553 --> 01:14:38,961
<i>Because anything we're not
is a thing we're taught to fear.</i>

582
01:15:07,742 --> 01:15:12,663
<i>So is that fear you're feeling right now?
Or is that something else?</i>

583
01:15:15,647 --> 01:15:17,655
<i>lt's fear.</i>

584
01:15:18,880 --> 01:15:21,117
<i>Of what you'll do?</i>

585
01:15:25,793 --> 01:15:27,964
Of what you think of me.

586
01:15:45,924 --> 01:15:49,634
<i>When l draw you, Ioup-garou,</i>

587
01:15:50,821 --> 01:15:53,025
<i>l'd wish that you were real.</i>

588
01:15:54,853 --> 01:15:58,716
So what right do l have
to wish you away now?

589
01:16:04,326 --> 01:16:05,919
You can control it.

590
01:16:06,759 --> 01:16:08,482
l can control it.

591
01:16:37,196 --> 01:16:40,230
Where would she hide, l asked.

592
01:16:40,301 --> 01:16:42,308
Where else but where l told her not to?

593
01:16:42,380 --> 01:16:45,676
<i>-Don't, Astrid.
-He's not one of us.</i>

594
01:16:47,566 --> 01:16:50,828
<i>Astrid, don't. There is another way.</i>

595
01:16:50,958 --> 01:16:56,458
lt was man who killed my sister.
lt was man who killed my son.

596
01:16:56,655 --> 01:16:59,208
lt was Gabriel that killed Rafe.

597
01:16:59,279 --> 01:17:04,015
<i>Just like he'll kill me.
lt's the only justice he knows.</i>

598
01:17:04,496 --> 01:17:07,758
<i>l'll protect you. l'll make him see.</i>

599
01:17:07,889 --> 01:17:11,501
<i>Just like you'll make him see
who he really belongs with?</i>

600
01:17:11,761 --> 01:17:15,242
Your first love all went wrong.

601
01:17:15,537 --> 01:17:18,407
<i>Please don't take mine from me.</i>

602
01:17:26,963 --> 01:17:29,517
ls that silver?

603
01:17:30,388 --> 01:17:32,690
<i>We're going to the pharmacist's.
We're getting antigen,</i>

604
01:17:32,756 --> 01:17:34,698
<i>and then we're leaving the city.</i>

605
01:17:36,725 --> 01:17:40,468
<i>He can't love you if he fears you.</i>

606
01:17:43,062 --> 01:17:45,878
Tell me not to fall in love, Astrid.

607
01:17:46,614 --> 01:17:49,648
Tell me how much more to life there is.

608
01:17:54,456 --> 01:17:59,159
Run, my little girl. Run free.

609
01:18:07,258 --> 01:18:08,949
Prescription.

610
01:18:15,131 --> 01:18:18,994
Hands on the counter.
Gabriel owns this guy.

611
01:18:21,660 --> 01:18:25,884
You must be in some kind hairy situation?

612
01:18:32,541 --> 01:18:35,924
Got some splinter in your paw?

613
01:18:38,847 --> 01:18:42,328
Like lemonade on a hot day.

614
01:18:59,746 --> 01:19:02,299
Stop! Drop the gun.

615
01:19:03,395 --> 01:19:07,257
Sorry, my furry friend. Drop the gun.

616
01:19:42,857 --> 01:19:44,384
Watch out!

617
01:19:50,698 --> 01:19:51,811
Run!

618
01:19:58,987 --> 01:20:02,283
How many of us have to die
for your happiness?

619
01:20:02,988 --> 01:20:04,931
l can smell him on you.

620
01:20:48,723 --> 01:20:52,401
You try to run a simple business...

621
01:20:55,604 --> 01:20:58,222
My new best customer.

622
01:20:58,421 --> 01:21:02,350
l want your antigen,
your bullets and your dust.

623
01:21:25,881 --> 01:21:28,728
How does it feel to be in a cage

624
01:21:28,825 --> 01:21:31,095
the way man would have you?

625
01:21:32,474 --> 01:21:35,508
You could have been
a great inspiration to your people.

626
01:21:36,698 --> 01:21:40,594
But look at you now. Our greatest shame.

627
01:21:44,604 --> 01:21:47,507
When you put your trust in man,
you condemn us all.

628
01:21:47,580 --> 01:21:49,042
We condemn ourselves.

629
01:22:03,583 --> 01:22:05,492
<i>Aren't we half-human?</i>

630
01:22:05,567 --> 01:22:08,731
<i>Don't you see that what you denounce
is a part of you?</i>

631
01:22:12,480 --> 01:22:14,520
<i>lt's not part of me. lt's part of you.</i>

632
01:22:14,592 --> 01:22:16,698
l know what l am.

633
01:22:20,001 --> 01:22:23,417
You and your traditions can go to hell.

634
01:22:25,410 --> 01:22:27,832
Well, you are the future of this pack.

635
01:22:28,515 --> 01:22:30,752
<i>l'll let you name her fate.</i>

636
01:22:51,174 --> 01:22:53,924
What have you ever loved, Gabriel?

637
01:22:54,023 --> 01:22:58,530
<i>Power, hate, fear?
You're the most human of us all.</i>

638
01:22:58,823 --> 01:23:00,133
You never understood.

639
01:23:00,200 --> 01:23:02,622
The ancient prophecy said a girl
from the bloodline of leaders

640
01:23:02,696 --> 01:23:04,354
would one day command us

641
01:23:04,424 --> 01:23:07,043
and lead us into a new age
of hope and glory.

642
01:23:07,561 --> 01:23:09,601
l thought that girl was you.

643
01:23:09,673 --> 01:23:12,390
And what will the new age of hope
look like?

644
01:23:12,457 --> 01:23:14,312
How much blood will there be?

645
01:23:14,378 --> 01:23:15,938
<i>Let's find out tonight.</i>

646
01:23:16,042 --> 01:23:18,792
We hunt, you and l.

647
01:23:32,301 --> 01:23:34,603
<i>Quick, he's there!</i>

648
01:24:59,771 --> 01:25:01,232
Drink up.

649
01:25:47,330 --> 01:25:51,935
For you and all mankind.

650
01:25:59,011 --> 01:26:02,143
You want to shoot your own family?

651
01:26:05,253 --> 01:26:08,734
You want to be that hunter
on that snowy night?

652
01:26:10,789 --> 01:26:13,473
Then l give you my back.

653
01:26:13,862 --> 01:26:16,383
<i>That's all you deserve.</i>

654
01:26:31,529 --> 01:26:33,023
Shoot him.

655
01:26:34,569 --> 01:26:36,064
<i>l can't.</i>

656
01:26:38,154 --> 01:26:39,780
Shoot him.

657
01:26:42,667 --> 01:26:44,227
<i>l can't.</i>

658
01:27:27,697 --> 01:27:31,080
Hey, Vivian! Vivian, help.

659
01:27:37,299 --> 01:27:40,234
May you know the age of hope
when you see it.

660
01:28:01,623 --> 01:28:06,163
<i>So how are we going to get out of the city
if they're watching everywhere?</i>

661
01:28:07,704 --> 01:28:09,777
<i>There's one place they won't be.</i>

662
01:28:30,715 --> 01:28:35,255
<i>This is my worId. These are my peopIe.</i>

663
01:28:37,469 --> 01:28:41,048
<i>They beIieve in prophecies and destinies.</i>

664
01:28:41,661 --> 01:28:43,701
<i>I beIieve we make our own.</i>

665
01:28:47,742 --> 01:28:49,530
Where are we headed?

666
01:28:50,015 --> 01:28:51,957
How about the age of hope?

667
01:29:00,000 --> 01:29:02,586
Either that or Paris.

